public abstract class SBWException
extends java.lang.Exception

This class is the base class of all exceptions used in the SBW API. It is derived from the Java Exception class, from which it inherits the Throwable.getMessage() method for obtaining the message associated with an exception. SBWException also provides other methods such as getDetailedMessage() and handleWithDialog().

All exceptions have a numerical code associated with them; this code is used to match up exceptions in other SBW language bindings (in particular, for the C language). The method getCode() returns the integer code assigned to this particular exception class.

Version:
1.0

Method Detail

handleWithDialog

public void handleWithDialog()
Displays information about this exception in a modal dialog. The user can click on the "OK" button to dismiss the dialog, or click on the "Details" button to see the detailed message (if any) associated with this exception.

handleWithDialog

public void handleWithDialog(java.awt.Component parentGUI)
Displays information about this exception to the user in a modal dialog. The user can click "OK" to dismiss the dialog, or click on "Details" to see the detailed message (if any) associated with the exception. The single argument, parentGUI, is used to set the parent GUI component for the dialog.

Parameters:
parentGUI - the component that is the parent of this dialog.

extractStackTrace

protected static java.lang.String extractStackTrace(java.lang.Throwable t)
Extracts a printable form of the stack trace for the given Throwable. This is used by subclasses of SBWException.

Parameters:
t - the Throwable for which to get the stack trace.

translateException

public static SBWException translateException(java.lang.Throwable t)
This takes a Throwable and checks whether it is a subclass of SBWException. If it is, it does nothing and simply returns it as an SBWException; else, it converts the Throwable into an SBWRawException.

Parameters:
t - the Throwable to translate

getCode

public abstract byte getCode()
Abstract method for obtaining the integer code associated with an exception. Each exception needs to define this method to return an appropriate value.
